g.text: <op>: edge element for the predicate of an atomic formula. See
an extension point for stripe skipping as well as specializations of the operator tag name
<arg>: one argument of an atomic formula. See
an extension point for stripe skipping as well as specializations of the positional argument
Positional rest arguments follow the ordinary positional arguments in atomic formulas in the normal-form serialization.
Slotted arguments follow positional arguments in atomic formulas in the normal-form serialization.
The main section of an atomic formula contains an operator edge and a collection of argument edges. Pre-fix operator...
Atomic formulas may have an optional closure attribute.
